-- RBS May Drop Hoare Govett as Broker, Independent on Sunday Says
-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 2012-05-27T14:42:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-27/rbs-may-drop-hoare-govett-as-broker-independent-on-sunday-says.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Plc is
preparing to drop Hoare Govett as its corporate broker, after
selling the unit to  Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF)  in February, the
 Independent on Sunday  reported, citing an unnamed banking
source.  Rexam Plc (REX)  has replaced Hoare Govett with  Credit Suisse
Group AG (CSGN) , the paper said, without saying where it got the
information.  RBS and Jefferies Hoare Govett declined to comment, the
Independent on Sunday said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
